### 1) Get access token (client_credentials) and copy the access_token from the response (or use the saved variable)
POST {{authBaseUrl}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials&client_id={{client_id}}&client_secret={{client_secret}}



### GET Orders from Gateway Auth Demo expected Status: 200 OK
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth-demo/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Post Order to Gateway Auth Demo
Post {{baseUrl}}/auth-demo/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
{
    "prop1": "value1"
}

### Get Order with id 1 from Gateway Auth Demo
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth-demo/orders/1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Put Order to Gateway Auth Demo Status: 200 OK
Put {{baseUrl}}/auth-demo/orders/1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
{
    "prop1": "value1"
}

